    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-08-14T18:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-08-14T18:00:00-05:00" n="589"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d589">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00112 European War 1939/6271: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Spain</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Hayes</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-08-14T19:00:00-04:00"
                            >August 14, 1942—7 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>738. Your 1029, August 5. As General Orgaz has kept Madrid Government informed of
                    all developments, Department has not considered it necessary to discuss with
                    Spanish Embassy here question of separate economic agreement for Spanish North
                    Africa. Do you have any special reason to believe that such discussion would be
                    advisable?</p>
                <p>Repeated to Tangier.<note n="49" xml:id="d589fn49">As telegram No. 148, August
                        14, 7 p.m.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
